    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="drain" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Drain Water In Fuel</title>
        <figure id="f3350007177" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK11/K11041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Water drain valve and priming pump</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Priming pump assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve assembly (closed position)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not smoke and keep fuel away from flames and sparks.
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>A hose can be connected to the water drain valve to aid fuel and water draining.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>If the amber Water In Fuel (WIF) light is lit, do the following:</para>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0703" count="1">Open water drain valve and drain water and fuel into a correct container clearly
                marked DIESEL FUEL.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push fuel primer pump until a water free stream of fuel comes out the water drain valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Close water drain valve and dispose of fuel and water properly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start engine and check for fuel leaks. If fuel is leaking turn off engine and repair
                leaks.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
